oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Park Family, 1898
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: unknown
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The Park Family brothers and sisters at the James Park house, corner of Cumberland Avenue and Walnut Street, Knoxville, TN. 1898. Seated, l-r: William Park (1807-1895); Sophia Moody Park (1809-1895) (Mrs. George M. White); Mary Park (1813-1900) (Mrs. George W. England and later Mrs. William S. Kennedy); Harriet Park (twin to Mary, 1813-1899). Standing, l-r: Margaret Park (1817-1892)(Mrs. James M. Welcker); Jane Park (1819-1897) (Mrs. Landon Bowie); and Rev. James Park (1822-1912).
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Group portraits; Families;
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Knox County Two Centuries Photograph Project
